text: Nystagmus is the uncontrollable movement of the eyes. When Zayne was born his eyes didn't dance, and that was one of the reasons that led us to believe he didn't have albinism as at then . How clueless I was (story for another day), then at 8weeks old his eyes started to jerk gently . that was when I went on to research this and learnt it is called nystagmus. His nystagmus became most apparent at 3 months old. The oscillations (movements back and forth) were large amplitute early on. Although now, The oscillations have since started to slow down and at times looks more jerky. Zayne has been able to find ways to nearly stop his nystagmus for short bursts of time when focusing on an object! His nystagmus is always worse when he is tired or if he feels visually fatigued or over worked! This might mean it's time for a nap or even just a visual break. Paying attention to these signs has helped us find the sweet spot for when to work on tracking and when to just relax! As time goes on his eyes will get stronger and he will be able to control the movements much better. Many people living with albinism struggle with nystagmus and impaired vision. About only 10% of albinos don't have nystagmus. However even people without albinism can also be born with nystagmus or develop it over time. as it is not relatively linked to just albinism  #fypviralシ #babylove #albinobaby #albinismawareness #tiktoknigeria I #babiesoftiktok #albinismisbeautiful  #foryoupage #albinomom

text: In late 2014, Zayn became visibly ill and during that entire time period from September 2014 to February 2015, Harry physically could not sing the word "weigh" in Little Things. He knew it was a sensitive area for Zayn and I think seeing Zayn the way he had gotten really bothered him. You can see Harry move the mic away from his face or move his head away from the mic sometimes whenever the word "weigh" came up because he just was avoiding it that heavily. On Four album release day, Zayn was too ill to attend so Harry sang all of Zayn's parts in Little Things and dropped weigh at both the soundcheck and live performance. In the months and years before this, Harry always sang "weigh" and once Zayn got better he picked it up again. Only in this time period did he drop it. Harry noticed early on (September) that something was not right. I think Zayn was closed off about his issues and didn't want to open up so this was one of the ways Harry tried to show he cared along with getting him water at every show. Harry admitted in a 2017 interview that "in the same way that I don't talk about stuff, other people don't always talk about stuff, and maybe that's how they deal with stuff" in relation to Zayn's ED. It's evident that he knew and was trying to show his solidarity with Zayn as best as he could. #harrystyles #zaynmalik #zayn #onedirection #1D #zarry #zarrystylik #harries #zquad #directioner
